parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS module can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The front brake lever becomes stiff or hard to pull
the front brake fails to engage
the brake pedal becomes solid and unresponsive
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the ABS warning light may or may not illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Contaminated or corroded brake fluid can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes spongy or soft
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the brake fluid is dirty or contaminated
the brake system requires frequent flushing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes solid and unresponsive
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the brake fluid is leaking
the brake system requires frequent repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The manufacturer's slow response to recalls and lack of available parts can put customers at risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to faulty brake systems.
symptoms: Customers experience delays in receiving recall repairs
dealerships lack available parts
customers are forced to wait for extended periods for repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the primary compensator can cause the motorcycle to lose mechanical power, bog, and drop voltage, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially in high-traffic areas.
symptoms: Clanking noise from the primary case
voltage drop
loss of mechanical power
bogging
rattling and vibrating compensator sprocket attached to the crankshaft.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front wheel bearing can cause the front wheel to lock up, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vibration or shutter in the front end of the motorcycle
metal-to-metal noises from the front wheel bearings
handlebars vibrating
and potential wheel lock-up.
